  </header>

  <main>
    <section>
      <div>
        <img src="images/placeholder.png" alt="Shrimp Gumbo from The Princess and the Frog" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>New Orleans-Style Shrimp & Sausage Gumbo</h2>
        <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
        <p>A rich, flavorful gumbo straight from Tiana’s dream restaurant menu. Perfectly spiced with shrimp, sausage, and the traditional “holy trinity” of vegetables.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div>
        <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>For roux:</strong> ½ cup flour + ½ cup oil</li>
          <li>1 onion, diced</li>
          <li>1 bell pepper, diced</li>
          <li>2 celery stalks, diced (the “holy trinity”)</li>
          <li>1 lb shrimp, peeled and deveined</li>
          <li>1 smoked sausage, sliced</li>
          <li>Cajun seasoning, to taste</li>
          <li>4 cups seafood or chicken broth</li>
          <li>White rice (to serve)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>Instructions</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Make the roux by combining flour and oil, stirring constantly until the mixture turns brown.</li>
          <li>Add the diced onion, bell pepper, and celery. Cook until the vegetables are soft.</li>
          <li>Add the broth, sausage, and Cajun seasoning. Simmer the mixture for a few minutes.</li>
          <li>Finally, add the shrimp and cook until just pink and cooked through.</li>
          <li>Serve the gumbo over hot white rice.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
  </footer>

</body>
